The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Max New York Life draws up growth plan
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Max New York Life draws up growth plan
          GARIMA SINGH NEOGY                               
	New Delhi, Nov. 23: Private insurer Max New York Life Insurance Company has raised its paid-up capital by Rs 350 crore to Rs 1,782 crore in the current financial year to fund its expansion plan.        
	We have our strategies in place for expansion and have infused fresh capital worth Rs 350 crore to set up 1,125 offices, taking the total number of our offices to 1,600, said Rajesh Sud, CEO and managing director of Max New York Life.        
	Max New York will also hire three lakh agents and over 25,000 employees over the next few months. It is part of Analjit Singhs Max group.        
	Though there is a slowdown, the insurance firm has recruited about 7,000 in this fiscal, taking its total staff strength to 15,000 in India.        
	At present, the private life insurance player employs 61,500 agents.         
	We are currently growing at about 65 per cent over last year. This is favourable when compared with the private life insurance industry, which has seen a 40-42 per cent growth rate this year, said Sud.        
	The company plans to increase its total paid-up capital to Rs 3,600 crore by 2011-12.        
	The insurer, which expects to improve its premium income four-to-five fold by 2011, has sold about 5.77 lakh policies in the first six months of the current fiscal.        
	It collected a new premium income of Rs 803 crore during this period against Rs 486 crore in the corresponding period of the previous fiscal.         
	Total premium income (including renewal premium) for the first half of this fiscal stands at Rs 2,652 crore.         
	According to the Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority, the Life Insurance Corporation of India has registered a 16 per cent fall in new premium income during the April-September period at Rs 19,090 crore.        
	Max New York Life has so far sold 31 lakh policies on a sum assured of Rs 86,300 crore.        
	The company is a 26:74 joint venture between Max India Ltd and New York Life.        
	To increase its penetration in rural areas, the company has recently tied up with Indian Oil Corporation (IOC) to sell products through the latters rural outlets.        
	Under the agreement, ioc will sell insurance products to the rural masses from its 2,000 Kisan Seva Kendras across the country.        
	The company has also joined hands with the Indian Railways for brand promotion.                                                                                                                                     
